response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Fizz Buzz\", \"description\": \"Write a function `fizz_buzz` that prints the numbers from 1 to n, where n is given as an input. Replace multiples of three with 'Fizz', multiples of five with 'Buzz', and for numbers which are multiples of both three and five print 'FizzBuzz'. If the number is not a multiple of either three or five, just print the number.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef fizz_buzz(n: int) -> None:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): An integer that represents the upper limit for printing numbers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Prints FizzBuzz sequence up to n.\", \"code\": \"\\ndef fizz_buzz(n: int) -> None:\\n    for i in range(1, n+1):\\n        if i % 3 == 0 and i % 5 == 0:\\n            print('FizzBuzz')\\n        elif i % 3 == 0:\\n            print('Fizz')\\n        elif i % 5 == 0:\\n            print('Buzz')\\n        else:\\n            print(i)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert '1\\n2\\nFizz\\n4\\nBuzz\\nFizz\\n7\\n8\\nFizz\\nBuzz\\n11\\nFizz\\n13\\n14\\nFizzBuzz\\n16\\n17\\nFizz\\n19\\nBuzz\\n22\\n23\\nFizz\\n25\\nBuzz\\n26\\n27\\nFizz\\n29\\n30' == ''.join(fizz_buzz(30).split('\\\\n'))\", \"assert '1\\\\n2\\\\nFizz\\\\n4\\\\nBuzz\\\\nFizz\\\\n7\\\\n8\\\\nFizz\\\\nBuzz\\\\n11\\\\nFizz\\\\n13\\\\n14\\\\nFizzBuzz\\\\n16\\\\n17\\\\nFizz\\\\n19\\\\nBuzz\\\\n22\\\\n23\\\\nFizz\\\\n25\\\\nBuzz\\\\n26\\\\n27\\\\nFizz\\\\n29\\\\n30' == ''.join(fizz_buzz(30).split('\\\\n'))\"] }"
